<div class="row g-4"><div class="col-12"><div class="Wrapper_wrapper__raXe4 Card_card__7rJy4 bg-body-secondary rounded-3 p-4 card position-relative ContentBlock_content__MOc3W"><h2 id="plant-stems">Plant Stems</h2><h4 id="xylem-vessels">Xylem vessels</h4><ul><li><p>The functions of <b>xylem</b> tissue in a plant are:</p><ul><li><p>Vascular tissue that <b>transports</b> dissolved minerals and water around the plant</p></li><li><p>Structural <b>support</b></p></li></ul></li><li><p>Their cell walls contain <b>lignin</b>, which enables the vessels to withstand the pressure created by the moving column of water</p></li><li><p>Xylem vessels form <b>long, hollow</b> straw-like structures that are formed by <b>dead cells</b> (due to lignification of cell walls)</p></li><li><p>This means that they <b>do not</b> contain any cytoplasm or organelles that could slow down the flow of water</p></li><li><p>There are small regions in the walls that are not lignified, known as <b>pits</b>, which allows for lateral movement of water and minerals between xylem vessels</p></li></ul><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="Xylem vessel elements" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="1213" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="Xylem-vessel-elements.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 48w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=64/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 64w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=96/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 96w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=128/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 128w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=256/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 256w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=384/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 384w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=640/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 640w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=750/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 750w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=828/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 828w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1080/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 1080w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1200/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 1200w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1920/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 1920w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=2048/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 2048w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=3840/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Xylem-vessel-elements.png 3840w" style="color:transparent" width="1100"/></div><p class="text-center"><i><b>Images of xylem vessel elements: A = photomicrograph (drawing) in longitudinal section (lignin is stained red), B = scanning electron micrograph (drawing) in transverse section, C = microscope image (drawing) in transverse section (lignin is stained purple)</b></i></p><p><b>Structure and Function of Xylem Vessels Table</b></p><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="Relating structure &amp; function in xylem vessel elements table" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="967" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 48w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=64/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 64w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=96/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 96w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=128/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 128w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=256/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 256w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=384/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 384w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=640/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 640w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=750/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 750w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=828/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 828w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1080/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 1080w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1200/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 1200w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1920/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 1920w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=2048/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 2048w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=3840/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Relating-structure-function-in-xylem-vessel-elements-table.png 3840w" style="color:transparent" width="1100"/></div><h4 id="sclerenchyma-fibres">Sclerenchyma fibres</h4><ul><li><p>Sclerenchyma fibres are not involved in transport of substances, they <b>provide support</b></p></li><li><p>Similar to xylem, they consist of bundles of <b>dead cells</b></p></li><li><p>They form <b>long, hollow tubes</b>, but they do have <b>end walls</b> present</p></li><li><p><b>Lignification</b> of cell walls occur, but they <b>do not have pits</b> like xylem vessels</p></li><li><p>They have <b>more cellulose</b> in their walls compared to other plant cells</p></li></ul><h4 id="phloem-tissue">Phloem tissue</h4><ul><li><p>The functions of <b>phloem</b> tissue in a plant are:</p><ul><li><p>Transport <b>organic compounds </b>(<span class="popovers" data-content="Substances that will become incorporated into biological tissue (e.g. sucrose in the phloem tissue)" data-title="Assimilates" data-toggle="popover" data-type="definition">assimilates</span>), particularly sucrose, from sources (e.g. leaves) to sinks (e.g. roots). The transport of these compounds can occur <b>up</b> and <b>down</b> the plant</p></li><li><p>This is known as <b>translocation</b></p></li><li><p>Phloem has no support function in a plant</p></li></ul></li><li><p>The organic compounds are dissolved in water to form sap</p></li><li><p>Phloem is a complex tissue made up of various cell types; its bulk is made up of <b>sieve tube elements</b> which are the main conducting cells and <b>companion cells</b></p></li><li><p>Other cell types of phloem tissue also include parenchyma for storage and strengthening fibres</p></li><li><p>Mature phloem tissue contains living cells, unlike xylem tissue</p></li></ul><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="Phloem sieve tubes elements and companion cells 1" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="1085" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 48w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=64/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 64w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=96/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 96w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=128/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 128w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=256/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 256w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=384/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 384w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=640/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 640w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=750/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 750w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=828/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 828w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1080/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 1080w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1200/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 1200w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=1920/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 1920w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=2048/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 2048w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=3840/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-1.png 3840w" style="color:transparent" width="1100"/></div><p class="text-center"><i><b>Structure of phloem tissue: A = microscope slide image (and below drawing) of a sieve tube element and companion cell in transverse section, B = photomicrograph image (and below drawing) of a sieve tube element and companion cell in longitudinal section</b></i></p><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="Phloem sieve tubes elements and companion cells 2" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="767" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 48w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=64/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 64w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=96/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 96w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=128/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 128w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=256/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 256w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=384/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 384w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=640/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/10/Phloem-sieve-tubes-elements-and-companion-cells-2.png 640w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=750/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/