bundles in a stem</h4><ul><li><p><b>Vascular bundles </b>consist of xylem vessels which are group together with phloem tissue</p></li><li><p>In a stem, the <b>xylem vessels</b> are always located towards the middle of the stem, while the <b>phloem</b> is located closer towards the outside of the stem</p></li><li><p><b>Sclerenchyma fibres</b> are associated with the vascular bundles and provide additional support to the stem</p></li></ul><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="transverse-section-through-a-stem" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="663" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="transverse-section-through-a-stem.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 48w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=64/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 64w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=96/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 96w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=128/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 128w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=256/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 256w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=384/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2022/04/transverse-section-through-a-stem.png 384w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=640/https: